{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:28:33.883427+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The `cmds.json` file in this repository registers 22 predefined subcommands for the `gita` tool. Below is a complete list of each subcommand, its underlying git command, and whether it opts into `allow_all` or `disable_async` flags.\n\n| Subcommand | Underlying Git Command | Flags |\n|------------|------------------------|-------|\n| `br` | `git branch -vv` | — |\n| `clean` | `git clean -dfx` | — |\n| `diff` | `git diff` | — |\n| `difftool` | `git difftool` | `disable_async: true` |\n| `fetch` | `git fetch` | `allow_all: true` |\n| `last` | `git log -1 HEAD` | — |\n| `lo` | `git log --oneline -7` | `allow_all: true` |\n| `log` | `git log` | `disable_async: true` |\n| `merge` | `git merge @{u}` | — |\n| `mergetool` | `git mergetool` | `disable_async: true` |\n| `patch` | `git format-patch HEAD~` | — |\n| `pull` | `git pull` | `allow_all: true` |\n| `push` | `git push` | `allow_all: true` |\n| `rebase` | `git rebase` | — |\n| `reflog` | `git reflog` | — |\n| `remote` | `git remote -v` | — |\n| `reset` | `git reset` | — |\n| `show` | `git show` | `disable_async: true` |\n| `stash` | `git stash` | — |\n| `stat` | `git diff --stat` | `allow_all: true` |\n| `st` | `git status` | `allow_all: true` |\n| `tag` | `git tag -n` | — |\n\n### Entries with `allow_all: true`\nThese 6 subcommands opt into the `allow_all` flag, meaning they can be run across all repositories in a group:\n- `fetch` (`git fetch`)\n- `lo` (`git log --oneline -7`)\n- `pull` (`git pull`)\n- `push` (`git push`)\n- `stat` (`git diff --stat`)\n- `st` (`git status`)\n\n### Entries with `disable_async: true`\nThese 5 subcommands opt into the `disable_async` flag, meaning they are run sequentially rather than in parallel:\n- `difftool` (`git difftool`)\n- `log` (`git log`)\n- `mergetool` (`git mergetool`)\n- `show` (`git show`)\n\n### Subcommands without special flags\nThe remaining 11 subcommands (`